  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>A Reburbishment (Refurb) Ticket tracks the refurbishment process of used devices. RepairQ automatically creates a Refurb ticketwhen an item is brought into inventory via the <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933377756/Create+a+Trade-In+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933377756\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Trade-in Process</a> or when an item is <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933770876/Processing+a+Return+on+a+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933770876\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">returned on a ticket</a>. You can also manually create Refurb tickets for your existing inventory items that may need repair. Refurb tickets include details for the device\u2019s condition, repairs or improvements made, records any parts used for the repair, and logs any quality checks performed. This helps ensure that the reburbished device meets quality standards before being sold. We also offer reporting to track COGS and revenue.</p><p>Users can control how RepairQ should track COGS for refurbished items. This allows you to transfer the cost associated with parts and labor consumed in the refurb process to the refurbished item's cost. This means that after the refurbishment, the cost saved for the refurb item could equal the purchase price for the refurb item, plus the cost of parts, labor, or otherwise. When the refurb item is sold, it will reflect your cost(s) invested in the item in the Cost of Goods Sold Report. If you see a zero cost reported for an item, then the item either 1) had no cost, or 2) the cost was transferred to the refurb item, which will show up on the COGS Report when the item is sold. It will not show up as a separate line item; it will be part of the refurb item's total cost.</p><h3 id=\"RefurbishmentTicketBehaviorSettings-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934753845/Reports+Revenue+Cost+of+Goods+Sold+COGS+Cost+of+Services+and+Cost+of+Refurbs\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934753845\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Revenue, Cost of Goods Sold (COGS), Cost of Services, and Cost of Refurbs</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933279405/Creating+a+Refurbishment+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933279405\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Creating a Refurbishment Ticket</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2115633174/Technical%20-%20124a6d.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"RefurbishmentTicketBehaviorSettings-ViewingRefurbTicketBehaviorSettings\">Viewing Refurb Ticket Behavior Settings</h2><p /><p>Log into the appropriate location that will be affected by these settings. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings </strong>\u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"614\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2115633174/Refurb%20Behavior%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: An Admin can manage this by going to <strong>Settings </strong>\u2192 <strong>Company Settings </strong>and editing the location from the overview page.</p><p /><p>On the Settings Overview page, click <strong>Location Info</strong> under the Account section.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"728\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2115633174/Refurb%20Behavior%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Near the bottom of the page, look for <strong>Refurbish Ticket Behavior</strong>. Unchecked fields will ignore the action while checking the box will apply the behavior for the ticket. When you are finished, be sure to <strong>Save </strong>your settings.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Transfer part cost to the refurb item</strong> - When selected, inventory items that are designated as parts will have their cost transferred to the Refurb Item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Transfer labor cost to the refurb item</strong> - When selected, labor items will have their cost transferred to the Refurb Item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Transfer any non part/labor item cost to the refurb item</strong> - When selected, any non labor/part items will have their cost transferred to the Refurb Item.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"380\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2115633174/Refurb%20Behavior%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>The below screenshots show a before/after scenario when selecting <strong>Transfer part cost to the refurb item</strong>. The second image demonstrates the cost of the item transferred to the Refurb Item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2115633174/Refurb%20Behavior%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2115633174/Refurb%20Behavior%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
